# {{ snake_name }} — App Quick Start

This folder is a deployable Kindling app. It imports domain code from the
`{{ package_kebab_name }}` package, but it is not itself a Python wheel.

## First run

The app ships with fixture CSV files under `tests/entities/`. When you run
locally (standalone Spark), Kindling loads those CSVs automatically instead of
reading from cloud storage — no credentials needed:

```bash
kindling app run .
```

Fixture files are named after the entity they seed:

| Entity ID | Fixture path |
|-----------|-------------|
{% if layers == "medallion" -%}
| `bronze.records` | `tests/entities/bronze/records.csv` |
{% else -%}
| `raw.records` | `tests/entities/raw/records.csv` |
{% endif %}
Edit the CSV to change the seed data. Once you're ready to read from real
storage, set your storage paths in `config/env.local.yaml` and remove (or
rename) the fixture file — the real provider takes over automatically.

